Ranked tournament

This is a ranked tournament and is only available for players with the rank 1-6.

This roughly translates to the in-game CS:GO ranks of Silver, Nova, Guardian, Eagle, Supreme or Global.

Tournament info

Free to enter 5v5 Competitive mode


Prizes:

  1. 1st place: $350 ($70 per player)
  2. 2nd place: $100 ($20 per player)
  3. 3-4th place: $25 ($5 per player)

General info

The tournament is fully automated, so make sure to have the latest patch downloaded before the tournament starts. You're required to play on the same Steam account that you've synced with your aimzonecup.com sports account.


Check-in opens 60 minutes before the tournament starts. After that, you have 45 minutes to confirm your participation or you may lose your slot to reserve teams. If you still haven't confirmed your participation before the tournament starts you will forfeit your participation altogether.


Go to lobby timer is 10 minutes, failing to join the lobby and take your slot in time will result in a def loss. The rest time between rounds is 5 minutes.


Please contact the support if you have any questions or need help signing up. Make sure to read through the full ruleset in the rules tab above.


Our tournament system is still in beta, so make sure to contact us with any feedback. Good Luck in the tournament!

Matches

a. Rounds: 30 Rounds (Fifteen as each side[Terrorists & Counter-Terrorists])
b. Victory Conditions: The first team to win 16 rounds wins the map and the round is over immediately.
c. Each individual round is 1:45 in duration
d. Starting side will be chosen by a knife round.
e. In case of a tie after the regulation rounds end (15-15), 6 extra rounds will be played. 3 rounds as Terrorists and 3 rounds as Counter-Terrorists. First team to win 4 rounds wins the map. [Repeat if necessary]
f. Extra rounds restart money: $10,000

Pausing

If you have a problem that prevents you from playing on, you are allowed to pause the game. You have to announce the reason before or immediately after you paused the game. Pausing the game without any reason will lead to penalty points (see Unsportsmanlike behaviour). If the problem can't be solved (max. 10 minutes pause time)

Stand-ins and roster changes

If you want to change your roster before the tournament starts, the creator an admin of the team can remove the team and you can sign up again - with the correct user.

If you need to change your rooster during an ongoing tournament. Contact the support asap so we can help you manually change your team. The change must be done during your 5 minute rest time, so be quick about it.

Winnings

Cash winnings from the tournament will be deposited to your Epulze account within 24 hours from when the tournament is finished.


If you lose by walkover you forfeit your winnings and will not be given any prize money.


For other prizes (digital and physical goods) youll get contacted by admins with information on how to claim your prize.

Raffles

Cash prizes from a raffle will be deposited to your Epulze account within 24 hours. For other prizes (digital and physical goods) youll get contacted by admins with information on how to claim your prize.

Joining the game

When a match starts you will receive a lobby invite in the CS:GO client. (If you dont allow invite from non Steam friends youre still able to join with lobby name and password provided in the pre-game view).


For 1v1 games you have 5 minutes to join the CS:GO lobby, failure to join will result in a default loss.


For 5v5 games you have 10 minutes to join the CS:GO lobby, failure to join will result in a default loss.


When all players have taken their slot in the CS:GO game lobby, the match will automatically start.


If your opponent doesnt show up, make sure you and your team are in the correct slots when the lobby closes. By doing so you will automatically receive a default win by walkover and move on to the next round of the tournament. Please note that all of your team members must sit in the correct slots or you wont receive a default win.

Other

For any other question you can always contact the support.

Breaching the rules

If Epulze or tournament Admins determines you are or may be in breach of any provision of these Rules, you or your Team may be subject to disciplinary action at Epulzes or the Administrators sole discretion, including, without limitation, disqualification, suspension, forfeiture of any and all compensation associated with the tournament, loss of pause time, prohibition from attending future Epulze events, suspension of your Epulze account, etc.

OMEN by HP

The OMEN advantage: A full line of gaming gear used by the pros. Whether you're a weeknight warrior or esports professional, OMEN PCs and accessories will help you elevate your game to the next level.

DXRACER

The company was founded in 2001, starting off as a manufacturer of car seats for luxury sports cars. Out of its inspiration and curiosity, DXRacer, the first and original brand of the modern gaming chair was born in 2006 and headed for the world of gaming and esports. The production began and years of innovation and investment in research and development has resulted in a wide product range, including several types of ergonomic gaming and office chairs with a refined racing inspired design.

As the leading premium brand of gaming chairs, DXRacer is world renowned and available on all continents with its headquarters in Michigan, USA.

Quality and design are our core values and we are always striving to go further in these domains. We put an honour in using nothing but high quality materials and maintain the high requirements set for all our products. Our products are manufactured with precision and respecting a strict high quality management.

NVIDIA

NVIDIA is the pioneer of GPU-accelerated computing. We specialize in products and platforms for the large, growing markets of gaming, professional visualization, data center, and automotive.

Our creations are loved by the most demanding computer users in the world gamers, designers, and scientists. And our work is at the center of the most consequential mega-trends in technology.

BETWAY

Betway Group, is a leading provider of first-class entertainment across sports betting, casino, bingo and poker. Since 2006 we have remained at the forefront of the online gambling industry, utilising the very latest technologies to provide innovitive and interactive gaming experiences in a secure environment.

Betway Group sponsors and partners with a wide range of international sports initiatives and events. These provide an opportunity to extend the message of our brand while supporting our values by sharing the thrill with our customers.

We're innovative, ambitious and passionate about what we do. We do it in a credible and responsible way, always aiming for the top.

DREAMTEAM

DreamTeam is the ultimate teambuilding and skill-growing platform that solves problems for hundreds of millions of gamers who want to find teammates, improve skills, manage teams, and earn money.

700k Players and Teams are looking for players like you. Join DreamTeam.gg today, create a player profile, and become part of the biggest CS:GO community.
